  "text": "DeeplabV3+ is one of the best performing semantic segmentation networks achieving the test set performance of 89.0% and 82.1% in PASCAL VOC 2012 and Cityscapes datasets respectively [CITATION_1] . DeeplabV3+ is an encoder-decoder network which makes the use of CNN called Xception-65 with atrous convolution layers to get the coarse score map and then, conditional random field is used to produce final output as shown in Fig. 8 . To train DeeplabV3+ on skin lesion dataset, we used a pre-trained model on PASCAL VOC 2012 and adjusted the final output of 21 classes to a single class for segmentation of skin lesion [CITATION_2] . It assigns semantic label lesion to every pixel in a dermoscopic image.",
